TITLE: Sam Bankman-Fried denied bail in Bahamas, ordered held until Feb. 8 in alleged FTX crypto fraud scheme
SUMMARY: A magistrate judge in the Bahamas has ordered Sam Bankman-Fried held until February, hours after a U.S. federal criminal indictment was unsealed

TITLE: Supply-Chain shortfalls targeted by new bill
SUMMARY: Rep. Ro Khanna (D. Calif.) and Sen. Marco Rubio (R. Fla.) are working to reduce supply chain by putting the Government in control of organizing the economy

TITLE: UK inflation eases, remains close to 40-year high
SUMMARY: While annual consumer price inflation dipped to 10.7% in November from 11.1% the previous month, inflation remains at levels last seen in the 1970s and early 1980s

TITLE: Biden administration plans to blacklist over 30 Chinese companies: report
SUMMARY: The U.S. Department of Commerce plans to add over 30 Chinese companies to a trade blacklist next week, according to a new report

TITLE: Bahamas jail where FTX's Sam Bankman-Fried reportedly heading is 'harsh,' rat-infested: State Department
SUMMARY: Fox Hill Prison, where FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried reportedly is heading following his arrest in the Bahamas, has "harsh" conditions and poor sanitation, the State Department says

TITLE: Fed slows interest rate increases with 50-basis-point hike, but signals more to come
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve enacted its seventh consecutive interest rate hike this year as it attempts to cool inflation without triggering an economic recession

TITLE: Sen. Elizabeth Warren, celebrity investor Kevin O'Leary clash over cryptocurrency, money laundering
SUMMARY: Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren got into a back-and-forth with FTX paid spokesman Kevin O'Leary during a Wednesday hearing over whether cryptocurrency facilitates money laundering

TITLE: US economy adds 263,000 jobs in November, better than expected as hiring remains solid
SUMMARY: The Labor Department's November jobs report provided a key snapshot of the labor market's health amid growing fears that the U.S. is headed for a recession

TITLE: US labor chief says poor immigration policy is 'biggest threat' to economy
SUMMARY: Labor Secretary Marty Walsh highlights the "threat" poor immigration policy presents to the U.S. economy while unpacking the November jobs report

TITLE: Biden signs bill forcing rail unions to accept agreement, averting crippling strike
SUMMARY: President Biden on Friday signed bipartisan legislation approved by Congress to prevent a railroad strike that could have crippled the U.S. economy
